      chapterActivity: 'A four-season biome walk in Central Park — one visit per quarter, tracking the ecotone between planted and feral and between southern and northern species at the park\'s latitude. Once a year, a longer field day in the Pine Barrens (Long Island) or the Catskills, with a dichotomous key and a collective attempt to identify 25 species without phones.',

