      chapterActivity: 'A one-night "constitution-writing" workshop at the Brooklyn Public Library, in which small groups draft a governing charter for a fictional thirty-person co-op and then argue about the amendment clause. Twice a year, a Saturday trip to Federal Hall on Wall Street (where Washington took the oath in 1789) and afterward a seminar-style discussion of Federalist 10.',

